    "notes": "High-fidelity detection pivot: tasklist.exe or wmic.exe spawned by a process located under C:\\Users\\*\\AppData\\Roaming\\* is strongly anomalous. The parent path (AppData\\Roaming\\Microsoft\\runtime_host.exe) is the primary discriminator vs. benign cases where parents are interactive shells (cmd.exe, powershell.exe) or known management agents (CcmExec.exe, msiexec.exe). Secondary signal: rapid sequential invocations (tasklist /v then /svc within seconds) from the same parent PID is a Fawkes ps command pattern. Tune out SYSTEM-context invocations from known management parents to reduce FP rate."
